question: give the list of live promotions
sql:
SELECT promotion_id, promotion_name, promotion_type, promotion_status
FROM promotion
WHERE promotion_status = 'ACTIVE'
FETCH FIRST 25 ROWS ONLY

question: how many active participants are there
sql:
SELECT count(*) AS value
FROM application_user
WHERE is_active = 1

question: give 10 random users info
sql:
SELECT user_id, user_name, first_name, last_name, user_type, is_active
FROM application_user
order by user_id
FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY

question: give top ten users who received most recognitions
sql:
SELECT
    au.user_id,
    au.first_name,
    au.last_name,
    count(cr.claim_item_id) AS recognition_count
FROM
    application_user au
JOIN
    claim_recipient cr
ON
    au.user_id = cr.participant_id
group by
    au.user_id,
    au.first_name,
    au.last_name
order by
    recognition_count desc
FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY

question: give top ten giver who recognized
sql:
SELECT
  au.user_id,
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name,
  count(c.claim_id) AS recognition_given_count
FROM application_user au
JOIN claim c
  ON au.user_id = c.submitter_id
group by
  au.user_id,
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name
order by
  recognition_given_count desc
FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY

question: give the address details of the user whose user id is 6051

question: who is the owner of the robert reagan and which node he belongs to
sql:
SELECT
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name,
  un.node_id
FROM application_user au
JOIN user_node un
  ON au.user_id = un.user_id
WHERE
  au.first_name = 'Robert' AND au.last_name = 'Reagan'
FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: give me the name of the node whose node id is 5007 and who is the owner the node 5007
sql:
SELECT
  n.name,
  au.user_name AS owner_user_name
FROM node n
JOIN user_node un
  ON n.node_id = un.node_id
JOIN application_user au
  ON un.user_id = au.user_id
WHERE
  n.node_id = 5007 AND un.role = 'OWNER'

FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY

question: Get the top 10 users who recognized others the most
sql:
SELECT
  au.user_id,
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name,
  count(c.claim_id) AS recognition_count
FROM application_user au
JOIN claim c
  ON au.user_id = c.submitter_id
group by
  au.user_id,
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name
order by
  recognition_count desc
FETCH FIRST 10 ROWS ONLY

question: Users who received recognitions in the last 30 days
sql:
SELECT DISTINCT
  au.user_id,
  au.first_name,
  au.last_name
FROM application_user au
JOIN claim_recipient cr
  ON au.user_id = cr.participant_id
JOIN claim_item ci
  ON cr.claim_item_id = ci.claim_item_id
JOIN claim c
  ON ci.claim_id = c.claim_id
WHERE
  c.submission_date >= sysdate - 30
FETCH FIRST 25 ROWS ONLY
